race.description: Wideline Windows & Doors Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: ANY QUESTIONS (2) showed early toe but couldn't finish the race off on debut over 1000m at Gosford 16 days ago. Draws a far better marble this time and the extra 100m helps. Expect a far better performance. Kim Waugh's debutante FROSTISEN (4) is a half-sister to Group 3 placegetter Bojangles. Trialling like a good horse so keep a close eye on the betting. CHEEKY SORT (9) resumes. Started favourite but disappointed at both runs in the maiden prep. May have more to offer this time in work. BOMB PERIGNON (6) will find this easier than the races she's been contesting this campaign, dropping to provincial level here third-up into the campaign. Can feature in the finish.
